summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 15560 entitled: "An ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of North 80th Street, in the City of Seattle, from Burke Avenue to Woodland Park Avenue, and providing for the taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor, and for the ascertainment, and payment of the just compensation to be made for the private property to be taken or damaged for said purpose, and for the assessment upon the property benefited, for the purpose of making such compensation", approved March 15, 1907.
